<inglise> COMMISSION DECISION of 27 October 1997 relating to the application of Council Directive 72/166/EEC on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to insurance against civil liability in respect of the use of motor vehicles, and to the enforcement of the obligation to insure against such liability </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS 97/828/E&Uuml;, milles k&auml;sitletakse n&otilde;ukogu direktiivi 72/166/EM&Uuml; (mootors&otilde;idukite kasutamise tsiviilvastutuskindlustust ja sellise vastutuse kindlustamise kohustuse t&auml;itmist k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta) rakendamist 27. oktoober 1997 (EMPs kohaldatav tekst) </eesti>
<inglise> (Text with EEA relevance) </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON </eesti>
<inglise> (97/828/EC) THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, Having regard to Council Directive 72/166/EEC of 24 April 1972 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to insurance against civil liability in respect of the use of motor vehicles, and to the enforcement of the obligation to insure against such liability (1), as last amended by Directive 84/5/EEC (2), and in particular Articles 2 (2) and 7 (3) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 24. aprilli 1972. aasta direktiivi 72/166/EM&Uuml; mootors&otilde;idukite kasutamise tsiviilvastutuskindlustust ja sellise vastutuse kindlustamise kohustuse t&auml;itmist k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta, (1) viimati muudetud direktiiviga 90/232/EM&Uuml;, (2) eriti selle artikli 2 l&otilde;iget 2 ja artikli 7 l&otilde;iget 3, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the present relationships between the national insurers' bureaux of the Member States, Norway, Switzerland, Hungary, the Czech Republic, Slovakia and Iceland as defined in Article 1 (3) of Directive 72/166/EEC ('bureaux'), which collectively provide for the practical means to abolish insurance inspection in the case of vehicles normally based in the territories of those countries, are governed by the following agreements supplementary to the Uniform Agreement on the Green Card System between national insurers' bureaux of 2 September 1951 ('supplementary agreements') which were concluded: </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriikide, Norra, &Scaron;veitsi, Ungari ja T&scaron;ehhi Vabariigi, Slovakkia ja Islandi nende liikluskindlustuse rahvuslike b&uuml;roode tegevust, mis on m&auml;&auml;ratletud direktiivi 72/166/EM&Uuml; artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 3 (edaspidi "b&uuml;rood") ja mis koos pakuvad praktilisi vahendeid kindlustuse kontrollimise kaotamiseks s&otilde;idukite puhul, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on nimetatud riikide territooriumidel, reguleerivad j&auml;rgmised liikluskindlustuse rahvuslike b&uuml;roode vahel 2. septembril 1951. aastal rohelise kaardi s&uuml;steemi kohta s&otilde;lmitud &uuml;htset lepingut t&auml;iendavad lepingud (edaspidi "t&auml;iendavad lepingud"), mis on s&otilde;lmitud: </eesti>
<inglise> - on 12 December 1973 between the bureaux of the nine Member States and those of Austria, Finland, Norway, Sweden and Switzerland and extended on 15 March 1986 to the bureaux of Portugal and Spain and on 9 October 1987 to the bureau of Greece, </inglise>
<eesti> - 12. detsembril 1973. aastal &uuml;heksa liikmesriigi ja Austria, Soome, Norra, Rootsi ja &Scaron;veitsi b&uuml;roode vahel ning mida 15. m&auml;rtsil 1986. aastal on laiendatud Portugali ja Hispaania b&uuml;roodele ning 9. oktoobril 1987. aastal Kreeka b&uuml;roole, </eesti>
<inglise> - on 22 April 1974 between the 14 original signatories of the Supplementary Agreement of 12 December 1973 and the bureau of Hungary, </inglise>
<eesti> - 22. aprillil 1974. aastal eespool nimetatud 12. detsembri 1973. aasta t&auml;iendavale lepingule esialgu 14 alla kirjutanu ja Ungari b&uuml;roo vahel, </eesti>
<inglise> - on 22 April 1974 between the 14 original signatories of the Supplementary Agreement of 12 December 1973 and the bureau of Czechoslovakia, </inglise>
<eesti> - 22. aprillil 1974. aastal eespool nimetatud 12. detsembri 1973. aasta t&auml;iendavale lepingule esialgu 14 alla kirjutanu ja T&scaron;ehhoslovakkia b&uuml;roo vahel, </eesti>
<inglise> - on 14 March 1986 between the bureau of Greece and those of Czechoslovakia and Hungary; </inglise>
<eesti> - 14. m&auml;rtsil 1986. aastal Kreeka b&uuml;roo ning T&scaron;ehhoslovakkia ja Ungari b&uuml;roode vahel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Commission subsequently adopted Decisions 74/166/EEC (3), 74/167/EEC (4), 75/23/EEC (5), 86/218/EEC (6), 86/219/EEC (7), 86/220/EEC (8), 88/367/EEC (9), 88/368/EEC (10) and 88/369/EEC (11) relating to the application of Directive 72/166/EEC requiring each Member State to refrain from making checks on insurance against civil liability in respect of vehicles which are normally based in the European territory of another Member State or in the territories of Hungary, Czechoslovakia, Sweden, Finland, Norway, Austria and Switzerland and which are the subject of the Supplementary Agreements; </inglise>
<eesti> p&auml;rast seda on komisjon v&otilde;tnud vastu otsused 74/166/EM&Uuml;, (3) 74/167/EM&Uuml;, (4) 75/23/EM&Uuml;, (5) 86/218/EM&Uuml;, (6) 86/219/EM&Uuml;, (7) 86/220/EM&Uuml;, (8) 88/367/EM&Uuml; (9), 88/368/EM&Uuml; (10) ja 88/369/EM&Uuml; (11) direktiivi 72/166/EM&Uuml; rakendamise kohta, milles kohustatakse k&otilde;iki liikmesriike loobuma tsiviilvastutuskindlustuse kontrollimisest s&otilde;idukite puhul, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on m&otilde;ne teise liikmesriigi Euroopas paikneval territooriumil v&otilde;i Ungari, T&scaron;ehhoslovakkia, Rootsi, Soome, Norra, Austria v&otilde;i &Scaron;veitsi territooriumil ja mille suhtes kehtivad t&auml;iendavad lepingud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the bureaux have reviewed and unified the texts of the Supplementary Agreements and replaced them by a single agreement ('the Multilateral Guarantee Agreement') which was concluded on 15 March 1991 in accordance with the principles laid down in Article 2 (2) of Directive 72/166/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> b&uuml;rood on t&auml;iendavate lepingute tekstid l&auml;bi vaadanud ja &uuml;htlustanud ning asendanud selle &uuml;he lepinguga ("mitmepoolne garantiileping"), mis s&otilde;lmiti 15. m&auml;rtsil 1991. aastal koosk&otilde;las direktiivi 72/166/EM&Uuml; artikli 2 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud p&otilde;him&otilde;tetega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Commission subsequently adopted Decision 91/323/EEC (12) annulling the supplementary agreements requiring Member States to refrain from making checks on insurance against civil liability on vehicles which are normally based in the European territory of another Member State or in the territories of Hungary, Czechoslovakia, Sweden, Finland, Norway, Austria and Switzerland, replacing those supplementary agreements by the Multilateral Guarantee Agreement as from 1 June 1991; </inglise>
<eesti> hiljem v&otilde;ttis komisjon vastu otsuse 91/323/EM&Uuml;, (12) millega tunnistati kehtetuks t&auml;iendavad lepingud, millega kohustati liikmesriike loobuma tsiviilvastutuskindlustuse kontrollimisest s&otilde;idukite puhul, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on m&otilde;ne teise liikmesriigi Euroopas paikneval territooriumil v&otilde;i Ungari, T&scaron;ehhoslovakkia, Rootsi, Soome, Norra, Austria v&otilde;i &Scaron;veitsi territooriumil, ja asendati k&otilde;nealused t&auml;iendavad lepingud alates 1. juunist 1991 mitmepoolse garantiilepinguga; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the Commission adopted Decision 93/43/EEC (13) requiring each Member State, as from 1 January 1993, to refrain from making checks on insurance against civil liability in respect of vehicles which are normally based in the territory of Iceland and which are the subject of the Multilateral Guarantee Agreement between national insurers' bureaux of 15 March 1991; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjon v&otilde;ttis otsuse 93/43/EM&Uuml;, (13) milles kohustati k&otilde;iki liikmesriike loobuma alates 1. jaanuarist 1993 tsiviilvastutuskindlustuse kontrollimisest s&otilde;idukite puhul, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on Islandi territooriumil ja mille suhtes kehtib liikluskindlustuse rahvuslike b&uuml;roode vahel 15. m&auml;rtsil 1991. aastal s&otilde;lmitud mitmepoolne garantiileping; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the bureaux amended, on the basis of the addendum of 17 September 1993, the Multilateral Agreement so as to include the Czech Republic and Slovakia; </inglise>
<eesti> b&uuml;rood muutsid mitmepoolset lepingut 17. septembri 1993. aasta t&auml;ienduse p&otilde;hjal, et h&otilde;lmata selle reguleerimisalasse ka T&scaron;ehhi Vabariik ja Slovakkia; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Slovenia signed the Multilateral Guarantee Agreement on 12 September 1996, </inglise>
<eesti> Sloveenia kirjutas mitmepoolsele garantiilepingule alla 12. septembril 1996, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> As from 1 November 1977, each Member State shall refrain from making checks on insurance against civil liability in respect of vehicles which are normally based in the territory of Slovenia and which are the subject of the Multilateral Guarantee Agreement between national insurers' bureaux of 15 March 1991. </inglise>
<eesti> Alates 1. novembrist 1997 loobuvad k&otilde;ik liikmesriigid tsiviilvastutuskindlustuse kontrollimisest s&otilde;idukite puhul, mille p&otilde;hiasukoht on Sloveenia territooriumil ja mille suhtes kehtib liikluskindlustuse rahvuslike b&uuml;roode vahel 15. m&auml;rtsil 1991. aastal s&otilde;lmitud mitmepoolne garantiileping. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall forthwith inform the Commission of measures taken to apply this Decision. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad komisjonile viivitamata k&auml;esoleva otsuse kohaldamiseks v&otilde;etud meetmetest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 27 October 1997. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 27. oktoober 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> For the Commission Mario MONTI Member of the Commission </inglise>
